# API Documentation Discipline

- Any API endpoint created, modified, or removed must update `docs/api/<module>.postman_collection.json`.
- API docs must be valid Postman Collection v2.1 JSON (importable in Postman).
- Collection entries must include:
  - endpoint path
  - HTTP method
  - auth requirements
  - request payload
  - response payload
  - error responses
  - example request
  - example response
- For every `/api/v1/*` endpoint, document `X-Platform` and `X-Device-Id` as mandatory request headers.
- Saved API test cases and documented success/invalid-format examples must exactly match the response envelope actually returned by handlers.
- Do not merge API changes without synchronized API documentation.
- Keep `docs/modules/<module>.md` synchronized with endpoint flow details (middleware -> handler -> service -> business outcomes -> response mapping).
